      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>There are so many things to know about Opitons Trading, you might have missed some of this month&#8217;s important news. Catch up with our most popular posts:</div>
<ul style='padding-left:10px;padding-right:10px;margin-top:15px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px'>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/find-options-trading-classes' style='color:#0000FF'>Find the Options Trading Classes Which Is Best for Your Needs</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Friday, December 4th, 2009 in <a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/?cat=4'>Options Trading Basics</a> &#8211; Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>There are several ways for a trader to gain better knowledge about <a title="options trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">options trading</a> if it’s a completely new financial instrument for him/her. Also as options trading is quite a rewarding financial instrument in the same manner it has a potential to drag a trader into heavy losses if he/she doesn’t know what they are up to.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/learn-basics-options-trading-tutorial' style='color:#0000FF'>Learn the Basics with Options Trading Tutorial</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Sunday, December 6th, 2009 in <a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/?cat=4'>Options Trading Basics</a> &#8211; Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>There is a learning curve involved before a trader starts trading options. To avoid the risk of losing huge amount of money one should try and learn the fundamentals and then trade options. Below is some of the important information for <a title="Option Trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">Option Trading</a> beginners:What are Options?Option is a contract between a buyer and a seller which gives the buyer of the contract a right to either buy or sell the underlying asset at a particular price before the contract end date.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/option-trading-newsletter-starters' style='color:#0000FF'>Option Trading Newsletter for the Starters</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Saturday, December 5th, 2009 in <a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/?cat=4'>Options Trading Basics</a> &#8211; Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>We have discussed in earlier blog that options are quite a rewarding financial instrument however it has a potential to drag a trader into heavy losses if he/she doesn’t know what they are up to. For the same its better for a new trader to be aware about the fundamentals of options before he/she actually starts trading, below mentioned are different ways how one can get more information about options trading:1.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/options-paper-trading-great-learning-tool' style='color:#0000FF'>Options Paper Trading a Great Learning Tool</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Thursday, December 3rd, 2009 in <a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/?cat=4'>Options Trading Basics</a> &#8211; Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>Trading in Options without understanding the fundamentals can be dangerous for your investment portfolio. At times there are situations where traders buy call options and to square off their positions instead of selling call options they buy put options which can bring in losses for them. To avoid this kind of situations paper trading becomes a great learning tool for the starters.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-system/trading-options-online-comfort-convenience' style='color:#0000FF'>Trading Options Online at Your Comfort and Convenience</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Wednesday, December 2nd, 2009 in <a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/?cat=8'>Options Trading System</a> &#8211; Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>Any trader would firstly need to look at all the available financial instruments before deciding the one which best suits his/her current portfolio. He/she can look at the advantages, disadvantages, risks, revenue and expenses of all the instruments. If a trader has decided to trade in options, then he/she needs to decide the medium of trading that is offline options trading (through  the phone) or online options trading(over the internet).</div>
</li>
</ul>
<div>Which post was your favorite? Let us know below!</div>
