      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>There are several online and in class <a title="Options Trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">Options Trading</a> Course available today to take advantage of. As talked in earlier blogs it’s better to know the <a title="fundamentals of options trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/fundamentals-of-options-trading/">fundamentals of options trading</a> before you actually start investing your own money into it. Ignorance is not bliss for options, and if it has a potential to give handsome returns then it also has power to drag the trader into heavy losses if he doesn’t have enough knowledge. For example: Options are quite different from stocks, so if a trader doesn’t have options trading knowledge and if he is bearish about the market then he might choose to sell call options when put options can be bought instead.</p>
<p>Different courses have different emphasis on the range of options topic:</p>
<p>1.)    <strong>Basics or Options Trading Fundamentals</strong> – There are more courses available that are based on Basics or fundamentals of options trading in comparison to any other subjects. This is because of the reason that many traders only believe in gaining the basic knowledge of options trading that would make them ready for trade, and other trading subjects can be learned by practice.</p>
<p>2.)    <strong>Learning options trading strategies</strong> – This is also an interesting subject to gain knowledge upon. If options trading strategies are perfectly designed and employed then the options have power to offer unlimited returns with limited amounts of risks. This course teaches the different strategies that hedge funds and institutional investors use to hedge their risks as well as to take advantage of market opportunities.</p>
<p>3.)    <strong>Designing options trading strategies </strong>– No two traders have same type of beliefs or same appetite to take risks. So there are several courses available where apart from teaching the class what type of trading strategies traders use today they are also being helped in devising an options trading strategy which best suits their beliefs, risk appetite and current portfolio position.</p>
<p>4.)    <strong>Stock <a title="option trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">option trading</a></strong> – Options trading becomes more interesting if a trader also own the underlying asset so in this course the class is taught the different possibilities if one wishes to trade in a particular stock as well as its derivatives (options).</p>
<p>With the popularity of internet most of these courses are also offered online where class can learn options trading at their own comfort. Therefore considering one’s current understanding about options and considering their zeal to learn a particular subject they can choose the Options Trading Course that best suits.</p>
