      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Good knowledge is the key for trading options with handsome returns and hence option is not an instrument for ignorant investors. There are several ways how you can trade in options; it can be by calling a brokerage firm, by using a web based trading platform or by <a title="options trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">options trading</a> software. One of the most striking disadvantages of options trading by calling a brokerage firm is the time it takes. At times a trader may need to wait in the queue for his turn and during this time he might lose a trading opportunity especially if he is trading with thin margins.</p>
<p>In this article we will see Options Trading Software in detail. To take advantage of this Software based trading system there are couple of things that are most important for a trader that is a computer and an internet connection. If a trader has a computer and an internet connection then he can install the software and start trading from any part of the world. By trading through software, trader can see real-time changes and if he finds an opportunity in front of him he can take quick decision make a buy or sell trade and make profits out of it. This type of pace is not possible with a trader calling the brokerage firm waiting for his turn, asking the current price and then making a trade.</p>
<p>There is quite a good number of software available today in the market. Below are some of the key features of available software:</p>
<ul>
<li>Other than regular buying and selling functions these software’s also lets you put a trigger so even if you are not tracking the price of an option still the trade can be executed if it reaches a certain point.</li>
<li>One can also see different types of useful data such as today’s open price, yesterday’s close price, today’s high and low, volume of a particular instrument being traded and open interest.</li>
<li>At times this software also provides tips of current buying or selling opportunities.</li>
<li>Brokerage is being charged depending on the facilities that the trading software provides. So if it’s high-end software with lot of features and also provides tips then it will have high brokerage, where as if it’s trading software with simple buying and selling features it will naturally have less brokerage.</li>
</ul>
<p>A trader should choose the Options Trading Software that best suits his/her requirements, considering his options trading knowledge and brokerage expense.</p>
