      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>We have discussed in earlier blog that options are quite a rewarding financial instrument however it has a potential to drag a trader into heavy losses if he/she doesn’t know what they are up to. For the same its better for a new trader to be aware about the fundamentals of options before he/she actually starts trading, below mentioned are different ways how one can get more information about <a title="options trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">options trading</a>:</p>
<p>1.)    Attending Options Trading Classes.</p>
<p>2.)    Subscribing to <a title="Option Trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">Option Trading</a> Newsletter.</p>
<p>3.)    Options Paper Trading (Simulation).</p>
<p>4.)    Reading Options trading books, blogs and articles.</p>
<p>In this article we will look at Option Trading Newsletter in detail.</p>
<ul>
<li>New traders can subscribe to Newsletters to gain more knowledge about Options Trading. There can be two ways of learning a trade one is trial and error method and second is to gather enough knowledge before you actually start trading. While learning with investing your own money there is a huge risk of losing money, where as if you are fundamentally strong in options trading system it eliminates the risk of losing money because of ignorance.</li>
<li>There are varieties of Options Trading Newsletters available online. If you are subscribing to one of these newsletters then it saves your effort of going online and finding the information that you might require, instead of that with options trading newsletters information comes to the trader.</li>
<li>You might be thinking what kind of information can be found in these newsletters? Depending on your current understanding of options or trading in general you can choose the newsletter that best suits you. This would ensure that newsletters are being created keeping in mind the level of audience. Further, some of these newsletters are being authored by hedge fund managers or investment analysts managing huge funds of a financial institution. These authors would not only make sure that you understand options trading correctly but at times they also provide some valuable money making tips.</li>
</ul>
<p>Lot of these options trading newsletters are paid and lot of newsletters are also free especially the ones that are being sent by brokerage firms. Starters can choose the newsletter that best suit their requirements and current level knowledge.</p>
