      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Trading in Options without understanding the fundamentals can be dangerous for your investment portfolio. At times there are situations where traders buy call options and to square off their positions instead of selling call options they buy put options which can bring in losses for them. To avoid this kind of situations paper trading becomes a great learning tool for the starters.  Paper trading is a process where a trader can employ his/her real time trade beliefs without investing actual money. The activity of Options paper trading feels the same as you are investing in the real market. A trader can analyze the market, evaluate the technical charts or use his/her gut or belief and trade in options accordingly without any risk of losing huge money.</p>
<p><strong>Why Options Paper Trading is a Great Learning Tool</strong></p>
<p>Paper trading offers the benefit of performing a trade which is similar to how one trades real time. So if a trader is buying or selling an option it will be traded at the current market price, market fluctuations are being displayed in real time, current positions can be squared off and one can see if the portfolio is in profit or loss with paper trading. All this can be carried out without the risk of losing your own money. Additionally, since your actual money is not at stake you can follow your trading system or trading beliefs without any reactions of greed and fear. At times market fluctuations are such that greed and fear acts against your trading rules or beliefs, and in turn stops you from earning profits that your strategy deserves. And once you have tested your decisions and know the fundamentals and market movements of options you can start investing in the real market.</p>
<p><a title="Options trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">Options trading</a> have a potential where one can make a fortune; so if the option spread positions are taken correctly then there remains a limited risk and it offers unlimited returns on your investments. There are several free online simulations available where you can test your strategies before applying them to your actual investments.</p>
<script type="text/javascript" class="owbutton" src="http://onlywire.com/btn/button_3860" title="Options Paper Trading a Great Learning Tool" url="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/options-paper-trading-great-learning-tool/"></script><p>This Post via the <a href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com">Option Trade</a> blog where you can get very useful information about Options Trading.</p>
