      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>There are so many things to know about Opitons Trading, you might have missed some of this month&#8217;s important news. Catch up with our most popular posts:</div>
<ul style='padding-left:10px;padding-right:10px;margin-top:15px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;margin-bottom:0px'>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/advantages-trading-options' style='color:#0000FF'>Advantages of Trading Options</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Saturday, November 14th, 2009 in <a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/?cat=4'>Options Trading Basics</a> &#8211; Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>If advantages of any businesses or trading venture are being discarded they are mostly due to the risks involved. But with <a title="options trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">options trading</a> there are lots of opportunities to capitalize upon which people might overlook if they only think about the risks. Further, in any type of trade there is a feature of risk involved but what one should look at is how much profit one can gain out of the trade.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/fundamentals-of-options-trading' style='color:#0000FF'>Fundamentals of Options Trading</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Monday, November 9th, 2009 in <a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/?cat=4'>Options Trading Basics</a> &#8211; Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>Today’s investors have multiple financial instruments to choose from such as mutual funds, bonds, commodities, stocks and exchange traded funds. But the range of securities does not end there, one other type of instrument is known as ‘options’ which provides a great investment prospects for the traders.Below are some of the <a title="fundamentals of Options trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/fundamentals-of-options-trading/">fundamentals of Options trading</a>:1.)    Option is a type of contract between the buyer and the seller, where in buyer of the option contract has a right to buy or sell the underlying asset at a certain price but is not obliged.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/feel-options-trading' style='color:#0000FF'>Get a Feel of Options Trading</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Friday, November 13th, 2009 in <a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/?cat=4'>Options Trading Basics</a> &#8211; Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>I have heard a lot of people saying that “I want to quit my job and start working for myself and not for someone else.” One might have definitely heard about Options Trading, it is also a money making activity to consider while looking out for a business opportunity. Options trading offer excellent returns on your investments and remain to be hottest venture.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/jargons-aware-trading-options' style='color:#0000FF'>Jargons you need to be aware about while Trading Options</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Sunday, November 15th, 2009 in <a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/?cat=4'>Options Trading Basics</a> &#8211; Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>Even though there are lots of Financial Terms in general that one might not be aware about, but for beginners following are some of the most used terms:Option – is a contract which gives the buyer a right to either buy or sell the underlying asset at a predefined strike price before the expiration of the contract. Further, buyer of the contract has a right and not an obligation to buy or sell the underlying asset.</div>
</li>
<li style='padding-bottom:15px'><b><a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/options-trading-basics/facts-encourage-trade-options' style='color:#0000FF'>Some of the facts that would Encourage you to Trade Options:</a></b>
<div><small>Posted on Wednesday, November 11th, 2009 in <a href='http://www.optiontradebasics.com/?cat=4'>Options Trading Basics</a> &#8211; Comments: (0)</small></div>
<div>Some traders believe in only venturing into familiar waters and stay away from the unknown. So is the case while choosing a financial instrument for investment purposes. Traders are more comfortable with investing in equity since it’s easy for them to understand simple ups and downs in the value of equity in comparison to options trading which is relatively hard to understand.</div>
</li>
</ul>
<div>Which post was your favorite? Let us know below!</div>
