      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>While learning more and more about <a title="option trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">option trading</a> one can find out how beneficial they are for the traders. Of course this statement also proves the phrase right that more the knowledge one has about a particular trade more are the chances of making profits from it. Following are some of the important aspects of option trading that one should remember:</p>
<p><strong>Option Trading:</strong></p>
<p>Like equity, mutual funds, commodity and currency, Option is also a trading instrument. Option is basically a contract which gives the buyer a right to either buy or sell the underlying asset at a certain price within a particular time period. However, with this contract buyer does have a right to buy or sell but he/she is not obligated to exercise this right. This feature makes buying a stock much different from buying an option.</p>
<p><strong>Two Types of Options:</strong></p>
<p>A trader can either trade in Call option or Put option. Both of these options are contradictory to each other.</p>
<p>In Call option a trader gets a right to buy the underlying asset at a particular price within a particular time frame. Calls are also known as long positions, and a trader would be in profits only when the price of the underlying asset stays above the strike price.</p>
<p>In Put option a trader gets a right to sell the underlying asset at a particular price within a particular time frame. Puts are also known as short positions, and a trader would be in profits only when the price of the underlying asset stays below the strike price.</p>
<p><strong>Ways to trade option:</strong></p>
<p>There are two basic ways of trading option American and European, difference between the two falls at the date when these options can be exercised. As per the American way, a trader can exercise his buying or selling rights anytime between purchase date and the expiry date. While as per the European way, a trader can exercise his buying or selling rights only when the contract expires.</p>
<p><strong>Parties involved in option trading:</strong></p>
<p>In option trading there could be four different parties involved for the two different types of options. They are buyers and sellers of Calls and Puts respectively.</p>
<p>Options are speculative instruments that best works for the traders who like to take risks.</p>
