      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I have heard a lot of people saying that “I want to quit my job and start working for myself and not for someone else.” One might have definitely heard about <a title="Options Trading" href="http://www.optiontradebasics.com/Getting-Started-With-Options">Options Trading</a>, it is also a money making activity to consider while looking out for a business opportunity. Options trading offer excellent returns on your investments and remain to be hottest venture. One may ask what information you will require to get a better idea about options. Which features make options low risk investments? What are the different ways and strategies one needs to be aware about to gain maximum benefit out of Options Trading? Read further and discover about how this trading venture has an edge over other business undertakings.</p>
<p><strong>Options Trading Simplified</strong></p>
<p>This type of financial instrument is focused on the investors who would like to invest in a stock at a price higher or lower than the prevailing or current market price, that too for a certain time period. If a trader is bullish about the markets, he/she can look at a higher price for that stock by trading options. As there is a time period involved with this type of trading, investors can take their positions and wait for the markets to act in their favor within the stipulated time period.</p>
<p>While trading options if the trend is predicted correctly one can earn huge returns, however if the markets are unstable and it’s hard to predict that the markets are going to fall or rise one has to bear losses.</p>
<p><strong>Nature of Trading</strong></p>
<p>With options one can either choose to deal in a particular stock or multiple stocks from different sectors. For some who chooses to trade in one particular stock has more risks since fluctuations in the price of this particular company’s stock will directly affect their whole investments. On the other side they can choose to invest in multiple companies from different sectors, which help in keeping the bottom line in green even though some of the stocks are not performing in their favor.</p>
<p>Additionally, with options one can limit their risks by hedging their positions but still the possibilities to earn unlimited profit remains. It’s a great strategy to trade in options together with investing in the underlying asset. At times with options one can also find arbitrage opportunities with which you can earn profits with as good as no risk.</p>
